# Every specification pattern, under every scope.
#
# The point is coverage of the pattern surface -- the parser alternatives, the
# desugaring into temporal logic, and the Printer cases for each Spec node --
# rather than the truth of any individual requirement, so the trace this runs
# against is not expected to satisfy them all. Compile-only fixtures like this
# are checked by parsing and printing, not by executing.

data    a   : boolean;
data    b   : boolean;
data    c   : boolean;

# ── The sixteen pattern bodies, under `globally` ─────────────────────────────
globally, it is always the case that a holds;
globally, it is never the case that a holds;
globally, a eventually holds;
globally, a holds after 100 milliseconds;
globally, a holds in the long run;
globally, once a becomes satisfied it remains so for at least 2 seconds;
globally, once a becomes satisfied it remains so for less than 2 seconds;
globally, a holds repeatedly every 100 milliseconds;
globally, if a holds, then it must have been the case that b has occurred before it;
globally, if b and afterwards c within 100 milliseconds holds, then it must have been the case that a has occurred before it;
globally, if a holds, then it must have been the case that b and afterwards c within 100 milliseconds have occurred before it;
globally, if a has occurred, then in response b eventually holds within 100 milliseconds;
globally, if a has occurred, then in response within 100 milliseconds b followed by c within 200 milliseconds eventually holds;
globally, if b followed by c within 100 milliseconds have occurred, then in response a eventually holds within 200 milliseconds;
globally, if a has occurred, then in response b holds continually within 100 milliseconds;
globally, a holds without interruption until b holds within 100 milliseconds;

# ── The remaining five scopes ────────────────────────────────────────────────
before c, a eventually holds;
after c, a eventually holds;
while c, it is always the case that a holds;
between b and c, it is always the case that a holds;
after b until c, it is always the case that a holds;

# ── Time-bound shapes: within / after / between, and each unit ───────────────
globally, a eventually holds within 5 nanoseconds;
globally, a eventually holds within 5 microseconds;
globally, a eventually holds within 5 milliseconds;
globally, a eventually holds within 5 seconds;
globally, a eventually holds within 5 minutes;
globally, a eventually holds after 5 milliseconds;
globally, a eventually holds between 5 and 10 milliseconds;

# ── Scope nesting: a scope may wrap another scope ───────────────────────────
after b, while c, it is always the case that a holds;
